<SECOND>BC-Carrier Fire, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0658,170</SECOND>
<HEAD>Two Killed In Explosion And Fire On USS America</HEAD>
<HEAD>EDs: SUBS 4th graf bgng ``The victims ... '' to CORRECT name of town
to Ham Lake, sted Hamlake.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two crew members were killed in an explosion
and fire Saturday night aboard the aircraft carrier USS America
while the ship was operating in the western Atlantic, the Navy
announced Sunday.
   A statement issued by the Atlantic Fleet's Naval Air Force
headquarters in Norfolk, Va., where the America is based, said the
incident occurred about 7 p.m. EDT Saturday in carrier's No. 2 fuel
pump room.
   ``Shipboard firefighters successfully extinguised the fire with
no additional casualties,'' the statement said.
   The victims were identified as Petty Officer 3rd Class Richard
E. Childress, 22, of Ham Lake, Minn., and Airman Recruit Larry J.
Brunson, 19, of Akron, Ohio.
   ``An investigation into the cause of the explosion is now under
way,'' the Navy statement said.
   It said the America is continuing on her assigned mission, a
previously scheduled deployment to the Mediterranean Sea and Indian
Ocean. The ship left Norfolk on Thursday.
