<HEAD>Bus Crash In Honduras Kills 2, Injures 71</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TEGUCIGALPA, Honduras (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A bus crowded with vacationers from
neighboring Nicaragua lost its brakes, rolled off the road and
crashed into a hillside Sunday, killing at least two people and
injuring 71, authorities said.
   All victims were believed to be Nicaraguan.
   The crash occurred early Sunday near Taulabe, 74 miles northwest
of Tegucigalpa, said Lt. Ernesto Ruiz of the Honduran fire
department.
   He said 73 people were on board the bus.
   The injured were rushed to hospitals in the nearby towns of
Siguatepeque, Comayagua and the Enrique Soto Cano air force base,
where a contingent of U.S. troops is stationed. Some of the
critically injured were taken in U.S. Army helicopters to the
capital, Ruiz said.
   It took rescue workers nearly two hours to pull the injured from
the wreckage, he said.
