<HEAD>Palestinian Shoots Two Policemen Before Being Wounded</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Israel, Bjt</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By SERGEI SHARGORODSKY</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Palestinian man shot at a police jeep in
northern Israel Sunday, wounding two Israeli officers before being
shot and wounded himself, hospital officials and Israel radio
reported.
   In the occupied lands, two Palestinians accused of collaborating
with Israel were reported killed by fellow Palestinians.
   Also Sunday, Israeli soldiers shot and wounded at least 21
Arabs, mostly teen-agers, in stone-throwing clashes, and a
10-year-old boy was injured by a rubber bullet, Arab hospital
reports said.
   An assailant opened fire with a pistol on the police vehicle
near Hefzi Bah, a settlement 50 miles northest of Jerusalem, Israel
radio and hospital officials said. They said the vehicle was
carrying a bomb expert and a Civil Guard volunteer.
   The Palestinian, identified as being from the West Bank village
of Araba, jumped from roadside bushes and ``emptied the whole
magazine, standing there like a Rambo,'' the radio quoted one
officer as saying.
   The bomb expert drew his pistol and fired, wounding the attacker
in the stomach and head, the radio reported.
   ``This man lost a lot of blood from the head .... His condition
is hopeless,'' said Yossi Fahima, an emergency service medic. He
said the two officers suffered only minor arm wounds.
   A West Bank man, Hassan Awdeh, 60, died of stab wounds received
Saturday in the West Bank village of Kfar Salit, according to Arab
reports confirmed by the army. Awdeh was attacked by masked youths
who accused him of collaborating with Israeli authorities, the
reports said.
   In the Gaza Strip, Ahmed Ibrahim Fakawi, 22, was found dead near
Khan-Yunis. Fakawi died of stab wounds, and Israel radio said he
was suspected of being an army collaborator.
   More than 40 Palestinians have been killed as collaborators by
fellow Arabs.
   The latest deaths bring the number of Palestinians killed in the
17-month uprising against the Israeli occupation to 474. Twenty-one
Israelis have also been killed.
   In other violence, stone-throwing clashes erupted in seven Gaza
Strip refugee camps and towns, and Arab hospitals reported 18
wounded, mostly teen-agers. A 10-year-old was hit in the cheek by a
rubber bullet, they said.
   In the West Bank, three teen-agers were shot in clashes in
Nablus and the Balata refugee camps, doctors said. The army said it
was checking the reports.
   In southern Israel, Jews enraged over the death of a soldier
blamed on Palestinians stoned Arabs' vehicles, injuring one of the
drivers and damaging nine cars, witnesses said.
   The Jews mounted their attacks along a road from the Gaza Strip
to retaliate for the death of Avi Sassportaz, whose body was found
last week.
