<SECOND>AM-Brain Dead-Birth,0215</SECOND>
<HEAD>Baby Born to Brain-Dead Teen-Ager Dies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN BERNARDINO, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A premature infant born to a
brain-dead teen-ager has died, about 32 hours after her mother was
taken off life support following her birth.
   The baby, born seven weeks premature Thursday and suffering from
lung problems, died at 9:05 p.m. Saturday, said Jan Westerson,
nursing supervisor at San Bernardino County Medical Center.
   The child's mother, Tanya Marie Rivera, 15, was removed from a
respirator and died at 12:58 p.m. Friday.
   The child was named Tanya Marie by her grandparents, who had
argued in court that hospital officials were wrong in keeping their
daughter on life support.
   They said she should be allowed to die but backed off after
anti-abortion activists joined the debate and urged that the girl
be kept alive until her baby was brought to full term.
   The teen-ager was declared brain-dead March 15 after being shot
in the head, allegedly by her 16-year-old boyfriend, Benny Danny
Tapia. A witness has said the shooting was accidental, and no
charges have been filed.
   Tapia has been jailed in Long Beach, charged with killing a
21-year-old man in an unrelated incident.
   An autopsy was planned to determine the cause of the baby's
death.
