<SECOND>AM-People, Sub, a0704,0135</SECOND>
<HEAD>Eds: SUBS 2nd item to UPDATE with Manilow performing Sunday.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Barry Manilow returned to the Broadway stage
Sunday, one night after a stomach ailment forced the popular singer
to cut his concert short.
   ``I'm fine,'' the 42-year-old performer told the Gershwin
Theater audience after his opening number Sunday. ``I'm really fine
and I want to thank everyone for their concern.''
   Saturday evening, Manilow was rushed to Lenox Hill Hospital
after suffering a reaction to medication prescribed for a stomach
ailment, the singer's spokeswoman, Susan Dubow, said Sunday.
Manilow was stricken during intermission, and the second half of
the concert was canceled.
   ``He is feeling much better. I think he rested much better,''
the spokeswoman said.
   Manilow's Broadway run was recently extended to June 3.
