<FIRST>r f AM-Earns-Airlines     05-14 0112</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Earns-Airlines,0119</SECOND>
<HEAD>TWA Reports Widening of First-Quarter Loss</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Trans World Airlines Inc. said it lost nearly
$83.1 million during the first quarter, widening the shortfall it
suffered a year earlier.
   The nation's ninth-largest airline said its operating expenses
increased in the three months ended March 31, largely because of
higher employee costs.
   The carrier, which was taken private by takeover strategist Carl
Icahn last year, also said it had $16.3 million in charges that
primarily resulted from that transaction.
   TWA lost $52.5 million in the first quarter of 1988.
   The carrier reported revenue of $989.7 million in the first
quarter, compared with $920.2 million a year earlier.
</TEXT>
